subsection.def:
Instrument Meteorological
                    Conditions means weather precluding flight in compliance with the Visual
                Flight Rules;

licence
                    for public use has the meaning assigned to it by Article 73(3) of this
                Order;

lifejacket
                includes any device designed to support a person individually in or on the
                water;

nautical
                    mile means the International Nautical Mile, that is to say, a distance of 1
                852 metres;

night
                means the time between half an hour after sunset and half an hour before sunrise,
                sunset and sunrise being determined at surface level;

non-precision
                    approach means an instrument approach using non-visual aids for guidance
                in azimuth or elevation but which is not a precision approach;

parascending
                    parachute means a parachute which is towed by cable in such a manner as
                to cause it to ascend;

pressurised
                    aircraft means an aircraft provided with means of maintaining in any
                compartment a pressure greater than that of the surrounding atmosphere;

